(nDCacheTLBWays, power_pad).explanation: Increasing the number of TLB ways requires additional hardware structures and interconnects, which directly increases the power consumption of pad circuits needed for external connections;

(nDCacheTLBWays, power_switching).explanation: More TLB ways require additional comparators and selection logic that switch more frequently during address translation, directly increasing dynamic switching power consumption;

(nDCacheTLBWays, time).explanation: Higher TLB associativity can reduce TLB miss rates and improve memory access latency, potentially reducing overall execution time;
